An excellent idea, but definitely has flaws.

The  intelligence would have worked just as well. Fixed

Guards immediately terminating is silly and SOD breaking. Intruders that are not obviously armed or trying to hide can be challenged and ordered to turn back or detained. Shooting on sight is pointless and silly. fixed

The Dr.Ashe log is horrible and juvenile, it should either be rewritten heavily or just removed. Much better now.

The  one seems geared solely for shock value, with a vastly inflated casualty count. It also makes very little sense, why would an influx of immigrants to a country after collapse decrease poverty? The very people willing to immigrate to such a country are going to be poor and desperate themselves. I think it should be replaced, rewritten or removed.

That being said, I really love the idea. I especially like that  ones and vice versa. (Dreamer dies, but new SCP found and contained, Properties of SCP's found at risk of causing containment breach etc.) I've upvoted based on the assumption that the fairly trivial to fix flaws will be fixed. If you correct start to correct the flaws I and the above poster have pointed out my upvote will remain. Good luck, I really hope this one stays on the main list.

EDIT: Just to add my opinion, I like Dr. Thane's notes.

EDIT: As the article has been improved, I've decided to keep my upvote in place.





